Company Overview of Dr. Peng Telecom & Media Group Co., Ltd.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Dr. Peng Telecom & Media Group Co., Ltd., a telecom operator, provides broadband Internet access and applications services to residential and enterprise customers in China. It offers data center and cloud services; optimization services; home IoT products; and OTT ecosystem. The company, formerly known as Chengdu Dr. Peng Telecom & Media Group Co., Ltd., was founded in 1985 and is headquartered in Beijing, China.


Chaowaimen Building A19th FloorNo.26 Chaoyang Wai AvenueChaoyang DistrictBeijing,  610015ChinaFounded in 198538,135 Employees



www.drpeng.com.cn







Key Executives for Dr. Peng Telecom & Media Group Co., Ltd.


Dr. Peng Telecom & Media Group Co., Ltd. does not have any Key Executives recorded. 



Dr. Peng Telecom & Media Group Co., Ltd. Key Developments

Dr. Peng Telecom & Media Group Co., Ltd., Board Meeting, Jul 14, 2017
Jul 14 17
Dr. Peng Telecom & Media Group Co., Ltd., Board Meeting, Jul 14, 2017. Agenda: To approve the proposal of adjusting relevant prices of incentive plan of stock options and restricted shares; and to consider the proposal of adjusting exercise date of phase IV stock option initially granted by Li Jinkun and Yin Lixin.


Dr. Peng Telecom & Media Group Co., Ltd. Announces Cash Dividend for 2016, Payable on July 14, 2017
Jul 5 17
Dr. Peng Telecom & Media Group Co., Ltd. announced cash distribution for 2016. For the year the company announced cash dividend of RMB 0.165 (taxes included) per A share. Record date is July 13, 2017, ex-dividend date is July 14, 2017 and cash dividend payable date is July 14, 2017.


Dr. Peng Telecom & Media Group Co., Ltd., Special/Extraordinary Shareholders Meeting, Jul 14, 2017
Jun 30 17
Dr. Peng Telecom & Media Group Co., Ltd., Special/Extraordinary Shareholders Meeting, Jul 14, 2017. Agenda: To discuss the proposal of meeting conditions for public corporate bonds issuance; to consider the proposal of public corporate bonds issuance; and to consider the proposal of requesting Shareholders' Meeting to authorize the directorate and personages authorized by the directorate to fully handle relevant issues of this public issuance of corporate bonds.


